joy wong daniels transformative learning technologies laboratory home about publications projects people teaching media fablearn 2011 home people joy wong daniels joy wong daniels position alumni website website joy is currently a master's student in the learning design and technology program before she came to stanford she was the associate director of marketing at zeum san francisco's children's museum renamed children's creativity museum over the course of her career she has also worked in various industries including technology consumer products government and non profit joy graduated from the university of california irvine with a bachelor of arts degree in international relations and spanish she also studied in madrid spain and taught high school english in utsunomiya japan she is particularly interested in how ubiquitous access to technologies is changing the way that young people learn play make friends and connect with their communities people faculty visiting researchers phd students ma students ms students undergraduate students high school interns collaborators alumni transformative learning technologies lab school of education stanford university 520 galvez mall room 102 ceras building stanford california 94305 usa connect with us connect with us on facebook connect with us on twitter connect with us on youtube connect with us on flickr copyright 2011 all rights reserved top
